<section class="mbr-info mbr-info-extra mbr-section mbr-section-md-padding home-container" style=" padding-top:60px; padding-bottom:0px; ">
 <div class="container">
  <div class="row" style="padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 60px;">
   <div class="col-md-4">
    <h3 class="mbr-info-title mbr-section-title display-2 callout left-border">
     Because
     <br/>
     No One
     <br/>
     is Immune.
    </h3>
   </div>
   <div class="col-md-7 col-md-offset-1">
    <p>
     <strong>
      For the past 15 years
     </strong>
     ,  a new infectious disease has been discovered nearly every year, with an outbreak reported on nearly every continent. These threats of pandemic diseases, food-borne illnesses, climate change, and global trade and transit underscore the importance of addressing the complexity of infectious diseases and public health preparedness. It requires more than collaboration.
    </p>
   </div>
  </div>
 </div>
 <div class="container" style=" max-width:100%;width:100%; background-color:#efefef;">
  <div class="row">
   <div class="mbr-table-md-up">
    <div class="mbr-table-cell mbr-right-padding-md-up mbr-valign-top col-md-7 image-size" style="width: 35%; padding-left:0;">
     <div class="mbr-figure">
      <img src="assets/images/Homepage.jpg"/>
     </div>
    </div>
    <div class="mbr-table-cell col-md-5 text-xs-center text-md-left content-size">
     <h3 class="mbr-section-title display-2">
      COMBATING ANTIMICROBIAL RESISTANCE IN SOUTH AMERICA AND THE CARIBBEAN: IDI MEMBER ARMANDO HOET
     </h3>
     <div class="lead">
      <p>
       Antimicrobial resistance (AMR) is on the rise and unfortunately not every country is prepared to fight it effectively. Armando Hoet, professor and director of the Veterinary Public Health Program at The Ohio State University and member of the university’s Infectious Diseases Institute, is preparing nations to battle antimicrobial resistance.
      </p>
     </div>
     <div>
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://idi.osu.edu/news/amr-hoet">
       Read how Hoet influences policy in Latin and South America
      </a>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div>
 </div>
 <div class="container" style="padding-top:80px;padding-bottom:60px;">
  <div class="row">
   <div class="col-md-12">
    <h3 class="mbr-info-title mbr-section-title display-2 heading">
     Connect with the Institute
    </h3>
    <p>
     Through innovative alliances on campus and in the private sector, leaders in infectious diseases research help the Institute solve problems at a local, state, national and global level. Work with us to help advance discoveries and tackle the problems yet to be solved.
    </p>
    <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://engage">
     WORK WITH US
    </a>
   </div>
  </div>
 </div>
</section>
